Audacity commit ff60f598f3
Subject: Fixes 2 bugs in Nyquist: (1) Bug 2706 probably already has a workaround in place, but the original code called snd-samples with ny:all for the maximum length to retrieve, and now that ny:all is bigger than 32-bits, the value was getting truncated. This change fixes legacy code to be 64-bit-aware. (2) allows sounds to be accessed beyond their stop time even when they stop in the middle of a block of samples. For example, this Nyquist prompt no longer generates garbage or crashes: (setf idur 5000) (setf impulse (extract-abs 0 (/ idur *sound-srate*) (cue *track*))) (mult 0.01 (convolve *track* impulse))

